apps_logging_app.agents.base module¶

class apps_logging_app.agents.base.BaseAgent(config)[source]¶

Bases: ABC

Abstract base class for all agent implementations.

The BaseAgent defines the core lifecycle, threading model, and data-processing pipeline for agents. Concrete agents must extend this class and implement the abstract transformation and filtering logic.

Responsibilities of this class include:

  • Initializing and managing WorkingDataConnection instances

  • Monitoring and reading log files with rotation handling

  • Matching data via regular expressions

  • Executing database queries asynchronously

  • Sending processed data to producers

  • Managing agent lifecycle (start/stop) in a background thread

Each agent runs in its own worker thread and periodically processes configured log files according to the provided configuration.

Subclasses must implement the _data_connections_transformation_and_filtering() method.

Parameters:

config (BaseAgentConfig) – Configuration object used to initialize the agent.

start()[source]¶

Starts the agent.

This method starts the worker thread which will execute the agent’s processing loop.

Returns:

None

Return type:

None

stop()[source]¶

Stops the agent.

This method sets the stop event and waits for the worker thread to finish.

Returns:

None

Return type:

apps_logging_app.agents.data module¶

class apps_logging_app.agents.data.WorkingDataStatus(*values)[source]¶

Bases: Enum

Enumeration representing the lifecycle status of a WorkingDataConnection.

This enum is used to track the current state of a working data connection as it moves through the agent processing pipeline.

Possible states are:

  • READY: The data connection is ready to be processed.

  • QUERY_RUNNING: A database query is currently being executed.

  • UPDATED: New data is available and ready to be sent to producers.

  • EXPIRED: The data connection has expired and will be removed.

READY = 'ready'¶
QUERY_RUNNING = 'query_running'¶
UPDATED = 'updated'¶
EXPIRED = 'expired'¶
class apps_logging_app.agents.data.WorkingDataConnection(name, producer_type, producer_name, database_type=None, database_name=None, query=None, is_error=False, expired_time=None)[source]¶

Bases: object

Runtime representation of a data connection during agent execution.

The WorkingDataConnection is a mutable, working-state object created from a DataConnectionConfig. It holds intermediate and final data extracted from log files, query execution results, and delivery status toward producers.

Instances of this class are managed by BaseAgent and move through different states defined by WorkingDataStatus.

A working data connection may: - Be populated by regex matches from log lines - Generate and execute database queries - Store query results - Be sent to one or more producers - Expire after a configured time window

Parameters:

  • name (str) – Unique identifier for the data connection.

  • producer_type (str) – Type of the associated producer.

  • producer_name (str) – Name of the associated producer.

  • database_type (Optional[str]) – Type of the destination database, if any.

  • database_name (Optional[str]) – Name of the destination database, if any.

  • query (Optional[str]) – Query associated with this data connection, if any.

  • is_error (bool) – Whether this data connection represents an error condition.

  • expired_time (Optional[datetime]) – Expiration timestamp for this data connection.

set_ready_status()[source]¶

Sets the status of this WorkingDataConnection to READY if it is not expired.

It is used to mark the data connection as ready for further processing after a query execution has finished.

Returns:

None

Return type:

on_query_done(fut)[source]¶

Called when a query has finished executing.

If the query result is not equal to the current list of results, it updates the list of results and sets the status to UPDATED. If the query result is equal to the current list of results, it sets the status to READY. If an exception occurs during the query execution, it sets the status to EXPIRED.

Parameters:

fut (Future[List[Dict[str, Any]]])

Return type:

None

check_expired_time()[source]¶

Checks if the current time is greater than the expired time of this data connection.

If it is, it sets the status of this data connection to EXPIRED. If not, it does nothing.

Returns:

None

Return type:

None

apps_logging_app.agents.factory module¶

class apps_logging_app.agents.factory.AgentFactory[source]¶

Bases: object

Factory class responsible for creating agent instances.

The AgentFactory instantiates agents based on a raw configuration dictionary. It resolves the agent type using the global AGENT_REGISTRY, validates the configuration against the corresponding config model, and ensures that all required producers and databases are initialized before returning the agent instance.

This class centralizes agent creation logic and guarantees that dependencies are available at startup time.

static create(raw_config)[source]¶

Create an agent from a given configuration.

Parameters:

raw_config (dict) – A dictionary containing the configuration for the agent.

Returns:

An instance of the agent class with the given configuration.

Raises:

ValueError – If the agent type is unknown.

class apps_logging_app.agents.model.BaseAgentConfig(*, type, name, buffer_rows=500, path_files=None, producer_connections, fetch_logs_interval=120, execute_query_interval=600)[source]¶

Bases: BaseModel

Base configuration model for agent instances.

This model defines all common configuration options required by agents, including file monitoring, buffering behavior, producer connections, and execution intervals.

It also enforces validation rules to ensure consistency between path files and regex references.

Parameters:

  • type (str) – Type identifier of the agent.

  • name (str) – Name of the agent instance.

  • buffer_rows (int) – Number of log lines to read per batch.

  • path_files (Optional[List[PathFileConfig]]) – List of configured log files to monitor.

  • producer_connections (List[ProducerConnectionConfig]) – Producer connections handled by the agent.

  • fetch_logs_interval (float) – Interval in seconds between log fetch cycles.

  • execute_query_interval (float) – Interval in seconds between query executions.

apps_logging_app.agents.registry module¶

class apps_logging_app.agents.registry.AgentEntry[source]¶

Bases: Generic[C]

Registry entry describing a registered agent type.

The AgentEntry class represents a single entry in the global AGENT_REGISTRY. It associates an agent type with:

  • the agent implementation class

  • the corresponding configuration model

This indirection allows agents to be dynamically instantiated from raw configuration data, while preserving strong typing between agent classes and their configuration models.

Instances of this class are created internally by the register_agent() decorator and should not be instantiated directly by users.

Parameters:

  • config_model (Type[BaseAgentConfig]) – Pydantic model used to validate the agent configuration.

  • agent_class (Type[BaseAgent]) – Concrete agent class associated with the entry.

config_model: Type[C]¶
agent_class: Type[BaseAgent]¶
